<subSubSection id="C33834B7C766323BEC8347FA1F2CDC31" pageId="118" pageNumber="119" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="B55194E08D336F3F52395C45701740FF" pageId="118" pageNumber="119">Distribution</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C9E338165CF12DBAF432297CFE316582" pageId="118" pageNumber="119">
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="2166F4C804635B3256B9DE482C86D7AB" captionStart="Figure 115" captionStartId="F115" captionText="Figure 115. Distribution of Conostegia apiculata." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.67.6703.figure115" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/96473" pageId="118" pageNumber="119">115</figureCitation>
). Known from few collections in the Pacific coast of Colombia to Central Ecuador, 600-1800 m in elevation.
</paragraph>
<caption id="F822B15DFE6F6EFBF5F97C3CB3A474E5" ID-Zenodo-Dep="973872" doi="10.3897/phytokeys.67.6703.figure115" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/96473" pageId="118" pageNumber="119" start="Figure 115" startId="F115">
<paragraph id="0515A72028023149FBBFFCE97A5655FC" pageId="118" pageNumber="119">
<emphasis id="6BA2AFC80ED7B3A01649CB16592B736B" bold="true" pageId="118" pageNumber="119">Figure 115.</emphasis>
Distribution of 
<taxonomicName id="963B9F12824D63D1C6EC99852687FC94" authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Wurdack" authorityYear="1957" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia apiculata" order="Myrtales" pageId="118" pageNumber="119" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="apiculata">
<emphasis id="4C69CC9189CC4A1DEBC65CDC8D67D91C" italics="true" pageId="118" pageNumber="119">Conostegia apiculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="CD1ACE183BB133A800918D496045FC98" pageId="118" pageNumber="119">
This rare species can be recognized based on its indument of stellate hairs, long apiculate calyptras, and stout, exserted styles. The drawing made by Wurdack deposited at NY shows the lack of a filament geniculation in this species. Floral measurements made of an Ecuadorian specimen (
<emphasis id="306D25D5AA9B46E48BCB943FA8CBA378" italics="true" pageId="118" pageNumber="119">Toasa et al. 11350</emphasis>
- NY) show longer styles at least in that population than in 
<normalizedToken id="AC10F4969F110A82C4C9116D63F48D68" originalValue="Wurdack’s">Wurdack's</normalizedToken>
drawing.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
